reviews.review_text: Satisfaction Best Satisfaction ever - Weir really makes it when he introduces the band members!

RFK 86 My friend Mark Scoville and I were so beat up from the heat and the partying the day before that we decided to sit this day out until the sun went down. We got down to the stadium from Silver Springs by train and walked up to the gate ticketless. The guard did a Song Remains the Same (Lotta Fun)rock n roll fantasy wave on thru free admittance and we walked right onto the floor to catch a sweet "Baby Blue". But our efforts weren't rewarded until Jerry busted out an awesomely built screaming Terrapin. We were sent off to the echoings of Satisfaction-as we eyed the black hookers that surrounded the rough neighborhood outside a hot steaming JFK night.
